<A HREF="http://www.arcanemasters.org">Sanctus Arcanum</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/23/02 10:07:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HS</span><hr size=1> My 60 druid can solo the break in to HS.  In fact, he could solo it several levels ago.  If there are two of you, you definitely could do it.  Now soloing there would be risky.  Even at 60, I sometimes get 2 golems on a pull...not often but sometimes.  The bigger problems are that the golems/biles/sperms run.  They always run up the east steps which have a pit trap in front of them.  You also have no way out of the place unless you can get someone to come give you a port/TL out or you have a gate potion.<br>
<br>
Team up with a druid there at the entrance, and exp should fly and it takes care of all of the other problems I mentioned....they can root for crowd control if needed.<br>
<br>
It would be very difficult to go much past the entrance since there are times where you cannot avoid getting 4-5 at once, but you can get killer experience just doing the entrance mobs.<br>
<br>
-Galdaen<br>
Sun Clan of Warriors<br>
Solusek Ro<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaspit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aspit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 6:32:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HS</span><hr size=1> ok man i have some info for you..i leveld here from 52 to 59 and a few aa so i kinda know the zone =0.  The enterence is ok exp but you need to snare sperms..nothing else that spawns there flees...you also have the possibility of having 2 mobs at once since there are 2 ent pops that will aggro you everywhere but at the exact zone in spot.  at 60 you can solo pull every golem...the adds the above post talks about are if you pull from the east steps (false ones) and there happends to be a wanderer whose 51+ that will assist.  Your best bet when zoning in solo is to run up the north steps and fall off of the right side of them facing the door.  This drops you into the safe spot in the pit .  Once your there camp aggro and your ready to go.  you can solo pull every mob in the pit area with a bow very simply..you dont even have to be careful because everything is lower than 50.  Sperms will flee on you and get you killed btw so snare them.  <br>
<br>
Ok when you pull make sure you engage the mob at the very top of teh safe spot (the wall at top of the hill in the pit)  This will ensure you get no adds from roamers.  Mobs here ht for max of 561 so be ready for that..their melee is max 131 double and a mid 40s kick or so.  so once your at this point pull a mob eat the ht and break out your tod and start wuppin ass.  The one problem with the pit is that 90% of the mobs here will con light blue to you and also soloing here it will take you about 2k-3k hps to solo one depending on how fast your tod proces slow.  So either pray theres a pc corpse nearby to summon bandages off of (if your pvp server) or be prepared to click your bp about 2342336 times.  Also the only exit to the zone is behind drus...so bring some kind of gate potion or a rent a porter to get out...hell if you have a druid on a sep acct plvl yourself and port out later.<br>
<br>
<br>
aspit<br>
